Express is a frame work which sits on top of node.js's Webserver functionality
it adds helpful
utilities to Node.js’s HTTP objects; 

require("http");//this is used by expressjs 

Express is an abstraction layer
on top of Node’s built-in HTTP server

Main features of expressjs
--------------------------
routing, middleware

Competitors for express
------------------------
Meteor - Meteor is full-stack, running code on both client and server
Hapi.js

Express doesn’t come with any templating languages built
in, but it plays nicely with almost every Node.js-based templating engine


templating
-----------
EJS, PUG




response.sendFile("/path/to/cool_song.mp3");// used to send the file directly


redirect 
--------------
response.redirect("/hello/world");
response.redirect("http://expressjs.com");

get ip
-------------
request.ip

useful modules
morgan  --  logging component
body-parser
 ejs   -- view engine